#Create simple shell scripting

$0: script name
$1: first argument of command/file content
$2:second argument of command/file content
$#: total number of arguments provided
$@: list of all arguments provided

In Linux shell scripting, the if statement is a fundamental tool for decision-making

if [ condition ]; then
    # Commands to run if the condition is True
else
    # Commands to run if the condition is False
fi

Note: You must include spaces inside the brackets [ ]. For example, [ $a -eq $b ] works, but [$a-eq$b] will throw an error.
